comparison_summary: High conservation between human and mouse APH-1A with 94.2% sequence identity. Most differences are conservative substitutions that do not affect protein function. Critical transmembrane domains and catalytic residues are perfectly conserved.

Strong conservation between human and mouse Nicastrin with 91.8% sequence identity. The extracellular domain shows high conservation, particularly in the substrate-binding regions. Most differences are in non-critical loop regions.

Extremely high conservation between human and mouse PSEN1 with 96.7% sequence identity. All critical catalytic residues (Asp257, Asp385) are identical. Transmembrane domains show perfect conservation, reflecting the essential nature of this catalytic subunit.

Near-perfect conservation between human and mouse PEN-2 with 98.0% sequence identity. Only 2 amino acid differences, both conservative substitutions. This reflects the critical role of PEN-2 in Î³-secretase complex assembly.
